- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses how machine learning problems can be modeled as minimizing the difference between submodular functions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimization problems that arise in AI applications. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper involves combinatorial optimization and constraints. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper provides computational bounds and a hardness result on the inapproximability of the problem.
